    <article>

      <h3>Planetside 2 arrived at MLG Dallas With a Truckload of News</h3>
      <h6>3/22/2013</h6>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <p>MLG Dallas has come and gone, but it left something behind. Lead Designer Matt Higby dropped the long awaited details on the partnership between Major League Gaming and Planetside 2. Here are the main points that Matt shared in his recent interview at MLG:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Outfits(Guilds for you classic MMO raiders) will compete against other outfits</li>
            <li>Matches will be 48 vs 48</li>
            <li>MLG is helping to create ladders ingame for Outfits to compete in</li>
            <li>There will be weekly tournaments, along with finals at MLG Championship events</li>
            <li>Custom maps will be made based on areas in the world for competition, but will not be available outside of a tournament scenario</li>
            <li>Some weapons will be restricted from use in competitive games to maintain balance.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <%=image_tag('NewsPlanetside2.jpg')%>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>Matt provided a lot of answers to many questions that people have been wondering about since this partnership was announced back in January, but there are a few questions that have been raised since this news broke. Specifically,  How will any live event take place when the teams consists of 48 players? It is hard to see how any venue can hold that many players and computers, let alone find the floor space to make room for Planetside 2 along with its other gaming stations. One possible answer that I can think of to this would be that they would have a select number of players play live at an event, with the rest of the team supporting from home. Only time will tell as this game continues to rapidly evolve.</p>
      <p><a href="http://tv.majorleaguegaming.com/videos/100081-mlg-planetside-2-showcase-esports-announcements">Click here if you want to check out the video</a></p>    </article>

    <hr />

    <article>

      <h3>Planetside 2 at MLG Dallas</h3>
      <h6>3/14/2013</h6>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <p>The hype train has left the station as news about MLG Dallas is heading around the Internet. The Major League Gaming 2013 Pro Circuit Winter Championship will be heading to Dallas this weekend (March 16-17) to bring everyone some League of Legends, Starcraft II: Heart of the Swarm, and Call of Duty: Black Ops II action.</p>
          </div>
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <%=image_tag('NewsPlanetside.jpg')%>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>However, MLG will be bringing more than just another greatly anticipated esports event to Dallas. At MLG Dallas they plan on giving more details about its partnership with Sony Online Entertainment and Planetside 2. Not much has been announced so far from this partnership, outside from making it official, but they have come out to let everyone know that they will be displaying the official Planetside 2 gaming stations. This will give us a good glimpse of what is to come.</p>
      <p>It will be interesting to see how they bring this MMO style FPS to the esports scene. Team sizes, fighting areas, and rules are currently anyone’s guess. Therefore, it would be possible to see the standard 4v4 setup similar to other FPS games, or they could have teams with 8 to 13 players on each side. I look forward to seeing how this game will further develop and if it will push the envelope as another free to play, competitive, esports defining game.</p>
    </article>

