    <article>

      <h3>The First Month of the New Ranked System</h3>
      <h6>3/6/2013</h6>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <p>The new ranking system in League of Legends has been active for almost a month now, and I have to say, this is quite possibly one of my favorite additions since returning in 2011 after a long hiatus. The new system feels extremely forgiving, while still providing a huge challenge if you wish to climb up the ladder. Click after the jump for my full impressions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <%=image_tag('NewsNewRanked.jpg')%>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>According to the new way the system seems to be operating, it only takes about 4-5 wins earn yourself a spot in a division series. This is assuming of course that you are on a hot streak and haven’t lost a game. However, once you hit 100 points you to begin your division series. This division series provides a great sense of accomplishment as your next 3 matches in the series  will truly test your metal. During these three matches you get one shot to prove you should advance, otherwise you are tossed back down to earn your spot at the top of your division again.</p>      <p>I found the jungle timers that these apps provide quickly becoming one of the most useful and my favorite features of these two apps. You always have easy access to them, so if you’re not coordinated enough to remember the exact spawn time (or unable to do quick addition with multidigit numbers at a moments notice — most of us aren’t), you can tap an icon on the app, and it will provide a countdown, along with an alert sound the moment jungle monsters, such as red or blue buff, or global objectives, such as Baron or dragon respawn. These timers even work for inhibitors — something I’ve yet to see someone keep track of (at least in a solo-queue game)!</p>
      <p>Once you climb through Division I of your tier, the new ranked system really begins to pay off. While in Division I of your tear you need to obtain 100 points to begin a Promotion series. When you get to this Promotion series you will face what I would consider the most stressful moments of your ranked career. You are pushed into a best of 5, which in my opinion gives you a greater feeling of importance for each game. This is your time to advance, this is your tournament game, this is your chance to earn a shiny new rank.</p>      </p>    <p>Which of these two apps you prefer will be completely up to you to decide, and relies mostly on personal aesthetic preferences. MobaDroid excels more on having a clean and sleek interface while LeagueDroid, though not as pretty, contains more features. However, both of these apps are definitely worth at least a test run since they both offer free ad-supported versions and a paid ad-free version. </p>
      <p>The most exciting part about the Promotion series is if you come to the moment where you have won two, and lost two matches. The last match you play in the series is quite possibly the most stressful game you can have in ranked. However, if you are skilled (and lucky enough) to win,  It is one of the best feelings you can get while playing ranked.      </p>
      <p>The old ranking system was never able to provide this type of excitement. What you had with the old system was a number which would fluctuate from time to time and give you the feeling that you are just spinning your tires in mud. This new system definitely brings a lot of life back into ranked and the game as a whole. I look forward to what other changes Riot will implement into League of Legends, but for now all I can say is kudos to you Riot, I tip my hat to you this day.      </p>
    </article>

