      <h3>LeagueDroid and MogaDroid: League of Legends Guides at your Fingertips</h3>
      <h6>02/15/2013</h6>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <p>As a League of Legends player, you may use different websites to obtain guides on different champions, be it Mobafire, SoloMid, CLGaming, or LoLPro. However, when you’re in a game playing as a new champion, you might not remember the items you want to buy, abilities you want to level up, or in both of those cases, which order! Even alt-tab could be costly to you and your team, even when you consider yourself “safe” in the company of your turret. Check out two apps for Android phones to help you out with this problems after the jump.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="large-6 columns">
          <%=image_tag('NewsLeagueDroid.jpg')%>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>This dilemma is where two Android apps that have recently been brought to my attention shine — LeagueDroid, and MobaDroid. If you have an Android phone or tablet near you, you have a multitude of guides and other features available and easily accessible at all times.. Having these at your fingerprints allows you to keep your monitor focused on exactly where you need it, in case you need to respond to the game at a moment’s notice, while freshening up on your champion’s needs.</p>
